    <h1>Transactions</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Wikipedia &middot; <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Database_transaction"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>Database transaction</a> &middot; CC BY-SA 4.0</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>transaction</strong> is a sequence of operations that either all succeed (commit) or all fail (rollback). The ACID properties guarantee correctness: Atomicity (all or nothing), Consistency (valid state to valid state), Isolation (concurrent transactions do not interfere), Durability (committed data survives crashes).</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Two transactions interleaving with conflict arrow -->
